==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-chump.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌmp|-ʌmp]]

=== Noun ===
'''chump''' (''plural'' '''chumps''')
# {{cattag|US|slang}} the opposite of a [[champ]]; a [[loser]]
#:''Buck up, man. Don't be such a '''chump'''.''
# the smaller of two [[bully|bullies]]
#: ''I'll take on that '''chump''', and you fight the other one.''
# an un[[intelligent]] person; a [[blockhead]]
#:''That '''chump''' wouldn't know his ass from a hole in the ground.''
# a [[gullible]] person; a [[sucker]]; someone easily taken advantage of; the target of a scam
#:''It shouldn't be hard to put one over on ''that'' '''chump'''.''
# someone lacking good sense - especially considered so for being [[scrupulous]] or un[[selfish]]
#:''What a '''chump'''!  He could have kept that money!  Who would have known?''

====Synonyms====
* (''the opposite of a champ''): [[loser]], [[spoilsport]]
* (''the smaller of two bullies''):
* (''an unintelligent person''): [[blockhead]], [[idiot]], [[dope]], [[dolt]], [[dunce]]
* (''a gullible person''): [[gull]], [[sucker]], [[dupe]], [[sap]] 
* (''someone easily taken advantage of''): [[pushover]], [[patsy]]
* (''the target of a scam''): [[mark]], [[pigeon]]
* (''someone lacking good sense''): [[fool]] 

